The article discusses the theme and decorations for the third Christmas of the First Family in the White House. The theme for this year is "The Spirit of America," which pays tribute to the traditions, customs, and history of the nation. The decorations in different areas of the White House showcase various aspects of American culture and heritage. The article also mentions the inclusion of the Gold Star Family Tree, the timeline of American design in the East Colonnade, the Vermeil Room highlighting the generosity of previous First Ladies, the celebration of Presidents in the Library, the star-spangled trees in the East Room, the classic Christmas tales in the Green Room, the official White House Christmas tree in the Blue Room, the games in the Red Room, and the Gingerbread House in the State Dining Room. The article concludes by mentioning that the White House will be open for visitors to enjoy the decorations throughout December.